{%- comment -%}
  Session 2 placeholder. The chrome (header/footer/cart/newsletter/finder) now comes
  from layout/theme.liquid. Session 3 will build the real homepage as sections from
  the html-build/index.html prototype (hero slider, pillars, bestsellers, etc.).
{%- endcomment -%}

<main class="container" style="padding: 80px 24px; text-align: center; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;">
  <div class="eyebrow">Theme port · Session 2 of 10</div>
  <h1 class="display-l" style="margin-top: 18px;">Chrome is <span class="display-italic">live</span>.</h1>
  <p style="margin-top: 24px; color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">
    The Santai header, footer, cart drawer, newsletter popup, and Lash Finder modal now wrap every
    template via <code>layout/theme.liquid</code>. Try the Shop dropdown, the cart icon, the search
    icon (header overlay), the Lash Match quiz link in the footer, or tap to see the newsletter
    popup fire after 5 seconds.
  </p>
  <div style="display:flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: var(--space-5)">
    <button class="btn btn-accent" data-finder-open type="button">Find my lash</button>
    <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="{{ routes.cart_url }}">Open cart</a>
  </div>
  <p style="margin-top: 40px; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-muted);">
    Next session: product template + metafield design against your real lashes &amp; accessories.
  </p>
</main>
